text: hello this is chef john from food wishes
comm with ham and eggs so this was going
to be one of those what i had for
breakfast photo posts and then i decided
you know what just film it show the
whole thing usually when you order ham
and eggs
it comes separate a piece of ham and
some eggs are here we're going to
combine both those amazing ingredients
into one fabulous entity so what i'm
going to do is i'm going to take a
skillet on medium heat with a little bit
of olive oil you can use butter alright
I'm going to toss my ham in there and
I'm just going to cook it on this side
for about a minute or two I just want to
start it going we're going to cook it
mostly on the other side but I do want
to warm it through I'm going to flip it
over and I'm going to crack my two eggs
right on top of the ham by the way use
fresh eggs see how those eggs are
sitting up nice and perky that's because
they're fresh old eggs spread out and
you'll just have the yolk sitting on the
ham and all the rest of the way will
just kind of run around the outside okay
what I'm going to do is I'm going to
turn the heat down to medium-low I'm
going to cover it and the steam in the
pan is going to cook the top of the egg
and is that ham caramelizes and gets
sweeter and tastier it also insulates
the bottom of the egg so it doesn't get
browned and bitter you don't really want
a fry egg white dark brown it's just not
a pleasant flavor so this takes care of
that I'm going to finish this with some
cayenne some salt and some pepper that's
no surprise and we're going to transfer
this onto our plate alright so the yolk
should still be soft the white should
just be set throw on a couple pieces of
rye toast marble rye by the way hey
marble rye make up your mind and there
you go you dig in you got that beautiful
runny yolk the egg white is attached to
the ham in this beautiful marriage of
breakfast nirvana
alright so instead of being separate
they are together and in my opinion
superior so anyway next time you got
